# Cursor Rules — rare-rohit Monorepo
# Reflects current tooling: Tailwind v3 + Framer Motion v11 + TypeScript strict

## Project Identity
Personal monorepo. TypeScript strict everywhere. Zero JavaScript files.
apps/* = deployable apps | shared/* = pure TS source via @shared/* aliases

## Language Rules
- TypeScript ONLY — never create .js or .jsx files
- `import type` for all type-only imports (enforced by ESLint)
- No `any` — use `unknown` + type guards, generics, or `satisfies`
- No `!` non-null assertions — use optional chaining or explicit guards
- No `as` type assertions without comment explaining why

## Import Rules
- `@shared/ui`    → shared UI components
- `@shared/hooks` → shared custom hooks  
- `@shared/utils` → utilities, animations, cn()
- `@app/*`        → apps/wedding-website/src/*
- Never relative imports crossing package boundaries
- Import order enforced by ESLint (react → external → @shared → @app → relative)

## Tailwind Rules
- Utility classes only — zero inline styles (except Framer Motion transforms)
- Use `cn()` from @shared/utils for conditional classes
- Design tokens: saffron, maroon, gold, ivory, marigold, divine (from tailwind.config.ts)
- Custom classes in index.css: section-padding, card-divine, gold-divider, mandala-bg, etc.
- Never hardcode hex colors — always Tailwind tokens
- Mobile-first: base → sm: → md: → lg: → xl:
- Section titles: use `.section-title` class (not raw text-4xl etc.)
- Cards on dark bg: `.card-divine` | Cards on light bg: `.card-light`

## Animation Rules (Framer Motion v11)
- ALL variants from `@shared/utils/animations` — never define inline
- Interactive props: use `hoverScale`, `hoverLift`, `hoverGlow`, `tapPress` exports
- Scroll entrances: `whileInView="visible"` + `viewport={{ once: true, amount: 0.15 }}`
- Page transitions: `pageTransition` variant from animations.ts
- Stagger: `staggerContainer` (0.1s) or `staggerContainerFast` (0.06s)
- Always wrap conditional renders with `<AnimatePresence mode="wait">`
- Check `useReducedMotion()` — disable animations when true

## Component Rules
- Named exports (no default exports except App.tsx and page files)
- Props interface above every component
- One component per file, PascalCase filename
- Never import from `../../` across boundaries — always use aliases
- All user-visible strings via `useTranslation('namespace')` — zero hardcoded strings

## CSS Architecture
- `@layer base` — CSS vars, resets
- `@layer components` — reusable classes (card-divine, section-padding, etc.)
- `@layer utilities` — one-off overrides
- Use CSS custom properties (--color-gold, --font-display) for dynamic values in JS

## i18n
- Namespaces: common | home | story | ceremonies | schedule | gallery | party | travel | rsvp | faq
- Always update both en/ and hi/ simultaneously
- Typed t() via react-i18next.d.ts — if no autocomplete, types are broken

## Code Quality
- `npm run check` before every commit (typecheck + lint + format:check)
- No console.log in committed code (console.warn/error OK)
- No commented-out code
- No TODO without issue reference

## Forbidden
- .js / .jsx files (TypeScript only)
- `any` type
- inline styles except motion transforms
- hardcoded hex colors
- hardcoded EN/HI strings in JSX
- default exports (except App.tsx, page components)
- deep imports bypassing aliases
